    "tool.select.desc": "Selects a switch to open its configuration panel. Places nothing itself.",
    "tool.track.desc": "Connects two connectors of a cell. Drag to draw a whole line, or click to place the current form. R/T rotate the form by 45°, right-click opens the direction menu for curves.",
    "tool.switch.desc": "Steers trains onto one of two branches. The config panel sets the default branch and rules per destination or train class — only reachable destinations are offered.",
    "tool.signal_block.desc": "Cuts the track net into blocks. A train enters a block only when it is clear. The arrow shows the guarded travel direction; R/T pick it.",
    "tool.signal_chain.desc": "Like the block signal, but also reserves the next block ahead — so trains do not deadlock each other at crossings.",
    "tool.erase.desc": "Removes track, switches and signals under the cursor. Level-fixed track cannot be demolished.",
    "tool.source.desc": "(Sandbox) Places a train source on a connector. Trains depart here per the timetable.",
    "tool.sink.desc": "(Sandbox) Places a destination on a connector. A train counts as arrived once it reaches it.",
