    "level.k4_01_sortierwerk.name": "4.1 Sorting Yard",
    "level.k4_02_drei_ziele.name": "4.2 Three Destinations",
    "level.k4_03_mischverkehr.name": "4.3 Mixed Traffic",
    "level.k1_01_erste_fahrt.briefing": "Lay the track through and bring the train to EAST. One run, one goal — your first turn at the desk.",
    "level.k1_02_blocktakt.briefing": "Two trains, one line: place a block signal that holds the faster follower until the block ahead is clear.",
    "level.k1_03_dreier_takt.briefing": "Three trains at the same speed heading EAST. Keep the cadence clean — nothing grinds here if the sequence is right.",
    "level.k1_04_langzug.briefing": "An overlong train occupies several blocks. Secure the line so the fast follower only moves up once the middle block is truly free.",
    "level.k1_05_schnellzuege.briefing": "Two express trains crowd behind a slow train. Divide the line finely enough that no jam builds up into lateness.",
    "level.k2_01_ausweiche.briefing": "Opposing traffic on a single line: build a passing siding with two switches and signals so the trains can meet in the middle.",
    "level.k2_02_zielregeln.briefing": "Four trains, alternating to EAST and NORTH. Program the switch with a destination rule that sends each train to its goal.",
    "level.k2_03_doppelter_gegenzug.briefing": "The siding under continuous load: two meetings in a row over the same loop — the reservations must clear cleanly.",
    "level.k2_04_ueberholung.briefing": "The freight train crawls while the commuter has a tight due tick. Let the commuter overtake via the siding — a class rule at the switch controls it.",
    "level.k3_01_kreuzung.briefing": "Two lines cross. Secure the crossing area with chain signals so no train ever has to stop inside the junction.",
    "level.k3_02_doppelkreuzung.briefing": "The track layout is fixed — you only place signals. Block signals alone deadlock the trains; chain signals before the crossings break the knot.",
    "level.k3_03_kreuzungstakt.briefing": "Cross traffic in two waves over the same junction. Keep the chain signals in cadence so both directions arrive on time.",
    "level.k4_01_sortierwerk.briefing": "Freight trains to FREIGHT, commuters to CITY. A class rule at the switch sorts the traffic onto the right destinations automatically.",
    "level.k4_02_drei_ziele.briefing": "Three destinations, two switches in cascade. Stagger the destination rules so every train reaches its station without a detour.",
    "level.k4_03_mischverkehr.briefing": "A crawling freight train crosses the busy commuter line. Let the chain signals decide who goes first — the commuter due times are tight.",
    "station.OST": "EAST",
